dismissalComment.html: gets it right this time! perfect yorker on the stumps, Dalrymple fails to pick it up and he ends up playing down the wrong line, the ball hits the boot plumb in front of the stumps. Dead as a stone and up goes the finger, England five down

headshotImage.caption: Geraint Owen Jones player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Geraint Owen Jones player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: flat and quick, typical Malinga delivery, Jones comes down the track and gets hit on the pad, loud appeal and umpire Benson adjudicates in favour of the bowler, Jones was looking to get outside the line and clip it away towards fine leg but was done in by the extra pace of Malinga

headshotImage.caption: Tim Bresnan player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Tim Bresnan player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: fuller length delivery on the stumps, cutting in with the arm, ball stopped a bit after hitting the deck, Bresnan too departs looking to clip it away towards fine leg, missed the target by miles and the ball crashed into middle and leg, fast and straight - Malinga at his best

commentTextItems.html: short ball on the off stump, Sangakkara rocks back and punches to the cover fence, that brings up the victory and they have done it in style
driven on the front-foot to cover fielder
turning into the leg stump, turned away to deep mid-wicket
again a drive to mid-off, this time Plunkett fields and cheers from the crowd as he fields the ball

commentTextItems.html: pitched up on the off stump, Sangakkara drives to mid-off, Plunkett lets it go through his legs and ball reaches the fence
half-volley on the off stump, Sangakkara drives beautifully through covers and ball races away to the fence
driven through covers and an easy single taken
good length ball outside off stump, Jayawardene pushes on the front-foot, gets the outside edge to thirdman fence
short ball banged in, Sangkkara pulls and gets the top edge, ball falls short of the deep square leg fielder
bouncer high and over the batsman, called a wide
driven on the up through covers and an easy single taken

commentPreTextItems.html: Jayasuriya and Tharanga started smashing from the word go and under pressure the England bowlers lost their way, it was a top notch partnership, one that will stay at the top of the record books for some time to come. They added 286 runs in just 31.5 overs and the rest was mere formality. None of the England bowlers were anywhere near their best and in the end it was nothing less than a massacre.
It was clearly a one-sided contest but one worth watching, to relive the entire match please read through Will Luke's bulletin

milestones.description: Harmison has conceded the most runs in an innings (97) in ODIs for ENG, going past Derek Pringle's record of 83
Jayasuriya and Upul Tharanga's 286-run partnership is SL's highest for the 1st wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 237 between Atapattu and Jayasuriya
This is the highest match aggregate (645) involving teams England & Sri Lanka in ODIs
Jayasuriya and Upul Tharanga's 286-run partnership is the highest for the 1st wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 258 between Tendulkar and Ganguly
Jayasuriya and Upul Tharanga's 286-run partnership is SL's highest for any wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 237 between Jayasuriya and Atapattu
Marcus Trescothick has scored 33 fifty-plus scores in ODIs, the most for ENG breaking Graeme Hick's record

stories.title: Fletcher bemoans England injuries
stories.subTitle: Sri Lanka in England, 2006
stories.summary: Following England's crushing defeat to Sri Lanka yesterday Duncan Fletcher, the England coach, has bemoaned the glut of injuries to have affected his squad, while defending Andrew Strauss' captaincy in the light of a 5-0 whitewash

stories.title: Trescothick reflects the mood
stories.subTitle: England v Sri Lanka, 5th ODI, Headingley
stories.summary: The post-match formalities after Sri Lanka's amazing run chase at Headingley were played out with the surreal backdrop of the final throws of England's World Cup clash against Portugal

stories.title: Brilliant Jayasuriya leads Sri Lanka whitewash
stories.subTitle: England v Sri Lanka, 5th ODI, Headingley
stories.seoTitle: Brilliant Jayasuriya leads Sri Lanka whitewash
stories.summary: Sanath Jayasuriya and Upul Tharanga led Sri Lanka to a quite brilliant eight-wicket win in the final one-dayer against England at Headingley to secure the most comprehensive of whitewashes, taking the series 5-0 - with over 12 overs to spare

stories.title: England aim to score solitary win
stories.subTitle: England v Sri Lanka, 5th ODI, Headingley
stories.seoTitle: England aim to score solitary win
stories.summary:
All eyes will be on England as they line-up for another vital
international match on Saturday - whether anyone will be paying any
interest in the cricketers is another matter entirely
